Because other configuration management software are either too complicated or bloated.

JSON data:
{
  "accounts": {
    "add": [ {
      "login": "ed",
      "uid": "1000",
      "groups": "wheel,audio",
      "shell": "/bin/sh" }
    ]
  }
}

Recipe:
#!/usr/bin/env ash
set -efu
usercnt=$(get -e accounts -e add -l)
cnt=0
until [[ $usercnt -eq $cnt ]]; do
  set -- $(get -e accounts -e add -e $cnt \
               -e uid -u -p \
               -e shell -u -p \
               -e groups -u -p \
               -e login -u)
  cut -f1 -d: /etc/passwd | grep -q "$4" && return 0
  useradd -u "$1" -s "$2" -G "$3" -m "$4"
  cnt=$(($cnt+1))
done

Dependencies:
jshon
mk
POSIX shell

ed@Gimokod /usr/bin $ ls -la mk jshon busybox-static
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root 730456 Nov  8 03:57 busybox-static
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root  50504 Nov  8 03:58 jshon
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root 645208 Nov  5 17:02 mk

Yes right all components can be compiled to static binaries at under 2MB total space
